## Project structure

```
{{ project_name }}/
├── models/
│   ├── staging/        # raw → cleaned views (1:1 with sources)
│   ├── intermediate/   # business logic, joins, enrichment
│   └── marts/          # final tables exposed to BI tools
{% for mart in marts %}
│       └── {{ mart }}/
{% endfor %}
├── tests/              # singular data tests
├── macros/             # reusable SQL macros
├── seeds/              # static CSV data
├── snapshots/          # SCD Type 2 snapshots
├── analyses/           # ad-hoc analysis queries
├── profiles/           # warehouse connection profiles (not committed)
└── .env                # local env vars (not committed)
```

## Getting started

This project uses [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) for isolated dependency management — no global dbt install needed.
A `.env` file is pre-configured so dbt always finds the local `profiles/` directory.

```bash
# Create the virtualenv and install dbt (once)
uv sync
{% if packages %}
# Install dbt packages (once)
uv run --env-file .env dbt deps
{% endif %}
# Verify your warehouse connection
uv run --env-file .env dbt debug

# Run all models
uv run --env-file .env dbt run

# Run tests
uv run --env-file .env dbt test

# Build (run + test) — preferred for CI
uv run --env-file .env dbt build

# Run a specific model and its dependencies
uv run --env-file .env dbt run --select +my_model

# Run a specific mart
uv run --env-file .env dbt run --select tag:{{ marts[0] }}

# Check source freshness
uv run --env-file .env dbt source freshness
```

## Warehouse setup — {{ adapter }}

{% if adapter == "BigQuery" %}
Authentication uses Application Default Credentials (ADC). Set up once:

```bash
# Local development
gcloud auth application-default login

# Or use a service account key
export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="/path/to/service-account.json"
```

Add to your `.env`:
```
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=./profiles
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=your-gcp-project
```
{% elif adapter == "Snowflake" %}
Configure credentials in your `.env` file:

```bash
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=./profiles
DBT_PASSWORD=your_snowflake_password
```

Update `profiles/profiles.yml` with your account, user, role, warehouse, and database.
{% elif adapter == "PostgreSQL" %}
Configure credentials in your `.env` file:

```bash
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=./profiles
DBT_HOST=localhost
DBT_USER=your_user
DBT_PASSWORD=your_password
```

Update `profiles/profiles.yml` with your host, port, and database name.
{% elif adapter == "DuckDB" %}
No credentials needed — DuckDB runs locally.

```bash
# The profile is pre-configured to create local .duckdb files
# Just run:
uv run --env-file .env dbt build
```
{% elif adapter == "Databricks" %}
Configure credentials in your `.env` file:

```bash
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=./profiles
DBT_HTTP_PATH=/sql/1.0/warehouses/your-warehouse-id
DBT_TOKEN=your_databricks_token
```

Update `profiles/profiles.yml` with your host and catalog.
{% elif adapter == "Redshift" %}
Configure credentials in your `.env` file:

```bash
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=./profiles
DBT_HOST=your-cluster.us-east-1.redshift.amazonaws.com
DBT_USER=your_user
DBT_PASSWORD=your_password
```
{% elif adapter == "Trino" %}
Configure credentials in your `.env` file:

```bash
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=./profiles
DBT_HOST=your-trino-coordinator.example.com
DBT_USER=your_user
DBT_PASSWORD=your_password
```
{% elif adapter == "Spark" %}
Configure credentials in your `.env` file:

```bash
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=./profiles
DBT_HOST=your-spark-master.example.com
DBT_USER=your_user
```
{% endif %}

{% if add_env_config %}
## Environment configuration

This project includes a `generate_schema_name` macro for environment-aware schema routing.
In **dev**, models land in `dev_<custom_schema>`. In **prod**, they use the clean schema name.

1. Copy the example env file:  `cp .env.example .env`
2. Fill in adapter-specific credentials (see `.env.example` for docs)
3. The `generate_schema_name` macro in `macros/` handles dev/prod schema routing automatically

> Tip: never put secrets directly in `profiles.yml` — use `env_var()` and `.env` instead.
{% endif %}

## Common dbt commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `dbt debug` | Verify warehouse connection |
| `dbt deps` | Install packages from `packages.yml` |
| `dbt run` | Run all models |
| `dbt test` | Run all tests |
| `dbt build` | Run + test (preferred) |
| `dbt run --select +model_name` | Run a model with upstream deps |
| `dbt run --select model_name+` | Run a model with downstream deps |
| `dbt run --select tag:{{ marts[0] }}` | Run models by tag |
| `dbt source freshness` | Check source data freshness |
| `dbt docs generate && dbt docs serve` | Build and serve documentation |

## Conventions

- **Staging models** are prefixed `stg_<source>__<entity>.sql` — one per source table
- **Intermediate models** are prefixed `int_<entity>__<verb>.sql` — business logic layer
- **Mart models** are prefixed with the mart name (e.g., `{{ marts[0] }}_orders.sql`) to avoid dbt naming collisions
- YAML docs live alongside their models (`_models.yml`, `_sources.yml`)
- Secrets never go in `profiles/profiles.yml` — use `env_var()` calls and `.env` instead

